<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="257" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 186.3411/108:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Commander of United States Naval Forces in the
                                Eastern Mediterranean</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to Admiral <persName type="to">W. S. Benson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fiume</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-23">December
                                    23, 1918</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Adriatic 30. Unpleasant incident occurred at Spalato between Italian
                            destroyer Carabiniere and Slav population. Leading Jugo-Slav citizens
                            and Serbian officers prevented disorder. Have reports which will
                            communicate to Italian Admiral at Sebenico. Entirely local and no
                            further consequences expected but is typical of feeling between two
                            nations.</p>
                        <p>First meeting Naval Inquiry Committee December 22.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullard</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>